     <h2>Project Purpose</h2>
    <p>The purpose of this project is to create a fictional multi-page website for Nova Coffee Shop. The website will establish an online presence for the business, showcase the menu items, and allow customers to easily find the coffee shop's location and contact information.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The project involves creating a multi-page website for Nova Coffee Shop using HTML and CSS. The website will use a simple layout that is easy to navigate and features a clean, professional design.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>People Resources</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Project Manager / Developer: Frances Ramirez</li>
      <li>Instructor</li>
      <li>Classmates</li>
      <li>Potential website visitors (customers)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Desired Results</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Display all required webpages.</li>
      <li>Include working navigation links.</li>
      <li>Maintain a clean and professional appearance.</li>
      <li>Be responsive on different screen sizes.</li>
      <li>Meet all course requirements.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Priorities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Time</li>
      <li>Quality</li>
      <li>Budget</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Time</h2>
    <p>
      Project planning: August 10-12, 2026.<br>
      Website developement: August 13-27, 2026.<br>
      Testing and revision: August 28-30, 2026.<br>
      Final submission: September 1, 2026. 
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Quality</h2>
    <p>The project will be considered complete when the website functions correctly, all navigation links work properly, the pages display consistently, and all assignment requirements have been met.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Budget</h2>
    <p>There is no financial budget required. The website will be developed using free software tools such as Visual Studio Code and GitHub.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Exclusions (Out of Scope)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Online ordering</li>
      <li>Customer login</li>
      <li>Payment processing</li>
      <li>Mobile application</li>
      <li>Employee scheduling</li>
      <li>Inventory management</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Feedback &amp; Testing</h2>
    <p>Feedback will be provided by the instructor during project reviews and after assignment submissions. Classmates will also provide feedback on design and functionality. The website will be tested to ensure links work properly and each page functions as expected.</p>
